Sample collection.name: Sample collection
Sample collection.description: A procedure whereby biological samples for an experiment are sourced.

Extraction.name: Extraction
Extraction.description: Properties of the preparation steps which took place before the measurement was performed.

Chromatography.name: Chromatography
Chromatography.description: A separation method where the components are distributed between two phases, one of which is stationary, while the other moves in a definite direction.

Chromatography Instrument.definition: A chromatography device that dissolves a mixture in liquid mobile phase to separate the analyte to be measured from other molecules in the mixture and allows it to be isolated.

Autosampler model.definition: A piece of apparatus, consisting of a rotating circular tray containing a number of sealed vials, that is used for the automatic injection of samples during a mass spectrometry experiment.

Data transformation.name: Data transformation
Data transformation.description: A planned process that produces output data from raw data.

Metabolite identification.name: Metabolite identification
Metabolite identification.description: Identification of the breakdown products of a substance, either through chemical instability or the actions of enzymes within the body.
